LOCATION:LILLY LIBRARY
GEO:39.167909;-86.518974
SUMMARY:Declaration of Independence Curator Talks
DESCRIPTION:The Declaration of Independence: The Motives\, The Moment is 
 an exhibition exploring the journey taken by the nation's founders. How d
 id colonial leaders go from loyal subjects of the British empire to riski
 ng everything by becoming revolutionaries? Take an insightful tour of the
  exhibition from the curator\, with up close looks at Revolutionary War e
 ra correspondence\, books and manuscripts that influenced the revolutiona
 ries\, and media that spread the word about the declaration.  Light refre
 shments will be offered. Come learn something new about the nation's foun
 ding and have a snack in Indiana University's rare book library!  Tours a
 re offered at noon\, 1 p.m.\, and 2 p.m. RSVP requested for planning of r
 efreshments and staffing.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><em>The Declaration of Independence: The 
 Motives\, The Moment</em> is an exhibition exploring the journey taken by
  the nation's founders. How did colonial leaders go from loyal subjects o
 f the British empire to risking everything by becoming revolutionaries? T
 ake an insightful tour of the exhibition from the curator\, with up close
  looks at Revolutionary War era correspondence\, books and manuscripts th
 at influenced the revolutionaries\, and media that spread the word about 
 the declaration.</p><p>  Light refreshments will be offered. Come learn s
 omething new about the nation's founding and have a snack in Indiana Univ
 ersity's rare book library!</p><p>  Tours are offered at noon\, 1 p.m.\, 
 and 2 p.m. RSVP requested for planning of refreshments and staffing.</p>
